						Advanced Emissions Solutions, Inc. (ADES) Shares Bought by Wellington Management Group LLP					

						 July 11th, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Patrick Bannon 


							Filed Under: Finance - SEC Filing Articles 







Tweet










Wellington Management Group LLP raised its stake in  Advanced Emissions Solutions, Inc. (NASDAQ:ADES) by 21.5% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 489,593 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 86,476 shares during the period. Wellington Management Group LLP’s holdings in Advanced Emissions Solutions were worth $4,670,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Bank of New York Mellon Corp increased its position in  Advanced Emissions Solutions by 40.4% in the first quarter. Bank of New York Mellon Corp now owns 16,543 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $158,000 after buying an additional 4,757 shares during the period.  AXA purchased a new position in shares of  Advanced Emissions Solutions during the first quarter valued at approximately $529,000.  Renaissance Technologies LLC increased its position in shares of  Advanced Emissions Solutions by 134.8% in the fourth quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 63,400 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $586,000 after buying an additional 36,400 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, James Investment Research Inc. purchased a new position in shares of  Advanced Emissions Solutions during the first quarter valued at approximately $2,279,000. 64.51% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 
Advanced Emissions Solutions, Inc. (NASDAQ ADES) opened at 9.03 on Tuesday. The firm has a 50-day moving average of $9.48 and a 200 day moving average of $9.79. The company has a market capitalization of $199.31 million, a P/E ratio of 1.99 and a beta of 2.82. Advanced Emissions Solutions, Inc. has a one year low of $6.21 and a one year high of $12.25. 




Advanced Emissions Solutions (NASDAQ:ADES) last posted its quarterly earnings results on Monday, May 8th. The industrial products company reported $0.39 earnings per share for the quarter, missing the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.50 by $0.11. The firm had revenue of $7.39 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $12.40 million. Advanced Emissions Solutions had a return on equity of 107.77% and a net margin of 286.05%.  On average, equities analysts forecast that  Advanced Emissions Solutions, Inc. will post $2.57 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently declared a special dividend, which will be paid on Monday, July 17th. Shareholders of record on Wednesday, June 28th will be given a $0.25 dividend. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Monday, June 26th. Advanced Emissions Solutions’s payout ratio is currently 21.93%. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: This piece of content was  posted by Daily Political and is owned by of Daily Political. If you are reading this piece of content on another website, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of United States and international trademark and copyright laws. The legal version of this piece of content can be accessed at https://www.dailypolitical.com/2017/07/11/advanced-emissions-solutions-inc-ades-shares-bought-by-wellington-management-group-llp.html. 
ADES has been the subject of several analyst reports. Zacks Investment Research raised shares of Advanced Emissions Solutions from a “strong sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Tuesday, May 16th. TheStreet raised shares of Advanced Emissions Solutions from a “d-” rating to a “b-” rating in a report on Friday, April 7th. Finally, ValuEngine downgraded shares of Advanced Emissions Solutions from a “strong-buy” rating to a “buy” rating in a report on Thursday, June 15th.
In other Advanced Emissions Solutions news, Director Alan Bradley Gabbard sold 4,700 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Wednesday, June 28th. The shares were sold at an average price of $9.21, for a total value of $43,287.00. Following the completion of the transaction, the director now directly owns 41,638 shares in the company, valued at $383,485.98. The transaction was disclosed in a document filed with the SEC, which is accessible through the SEC website. Corporate insiders own  8.49% of the company’s stock. 
Advanced Emissions Solutions Company Profile
ADA-ES, Inc (ADA) develops, offers, and implements environmental technologies and provides equipment and specialty chemicals that enable coal-fueled power plants to meet emissions regulations by enhancing existing air pollution control equipment. ADA’s wholly owned subsidiaries include Advanced Emissions Solutions, Inc, ADA Intellectual Property, LLC and ADA Environmental Solutions, LLC.
